# The broker serves the SPA at the SAME origin as the portal API, so the app
# defaults to same-origin ('') and needs NO configuration in production.
#
# VITE_TESSERA_API_URL — optional override of the broker base URL, used when you
# run `npm run dev` against a separately-running broker. Leave it UNSET when the
# SPA is served by the broker itself.
# VITE_TESSERA_API_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8080
#
# VITE_TESSERA_DEMO — set to 1 for a no-backend preview (in-memory fixtures, dev
# sign-in). Storybook and tests use the fixtures client directly; this is only for
# running the app with `npm run dev` when no broker is available.
# VITE_TESSERA_DEMO=1
#
# Auth is never baked in: dev loopback sends a non-secret X-Tessera-Dev-Principal
# header; OIDC sends a verified bearer token. Both are supplied at runtime.

